http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Man-found-dead-in-private-bus/article14021617.ece

Tension prevailed for a while at Kempegowda Bus Station on Tuesday after a mechanic, who was conducting routine checks, found a decomposed body inside a private bus parked in depot no. 7. He raised an alarm and later alerted the police. The deceased is aged about 45 years and was found hanging from the overhead handrail of the bus.“Police have taken up the case and efforts are on to identify the deceased. No ID card was found on him. Police are also questioning the owner of Meenakshi Bus Travels who owns the bus,” a senior police officer said.A case of unnatural death has been registered in Upparpet police station.